    • org.research_software.citation.cff.model.objects.Reference

  • public final class Reference
extends Object
    Model element representing an additional reference to the software.
    Version:
    Citation File Format Version 1.0.3
    Author:
    Stephan Druskat <[mail@sdruskat.net](mailto:mail@sdruskat.net)>
    See Also:
    https://citation-file-format.github.io/1.0.3/specifications/#/references-optional

        Constructor for databinding.
        Parameters:
        dateDownloaded - The date the reference has been downloaded
        edition - The edition of the reference
        nihmsid - The NIHMSID of the reference
        location - The location of the reference (e.g., for art)
        databaseProvider - The database provider providing the reference
        dateAccessed - The date the reference has been accessed
        editors - The editors of the reference
        type - The reference type
        authors - The authors of the reference
        languages - The languages the reference is composed in
        translators - The translators of the reference
        commit - The commit hash for the version of the reference
        year - The year the reference has been published
        collectionTitle - The title of the collection containing the reference
        conference - The conference of which the reference is part
        senders - The senders of the reference (e.g., for personal communications)
        keywords - The keywords pertaining to the reference
        status - The publication status of the reference
        datePublished - The date the reference has been published
        number - The accession number of the work (multi-purpose for different reference types)
        format - The format of the reference
        copyright - The copyright information pertaining to the reference
        url - The URL of the reference
        locStart - The line number in the source code file where the reference starts
        collectionDoi - The DOI of the collection containing the reference
        repositoryCode - The URL of the code repository for the reference
        start - The page number where the reference starts
        month - The month in which the reference has been published
        locEnd - The line number in the source code file where the reference ends
        patentStates - The states for which a patent is granted
        licenseUrl - The URL pointing to the license text if the license is not included in the [SPDX License list](https://spdx.org/licenses/)
        collectionType - The type of the collection containing the reference
        scope - A string describing the scope of the reference in relation to the software
        issn - The ISSN of the reference
        department - The department where the reference has been produced
        issue - The issue of a periodical in which the reference has been published
        contact - The contacts for the reference
        volumeTitle - The title of the volume in which the reference has been published
        thesisType - The type of the reference, if it is a thesis
        publisher - The publisher which has published the reference
        version - The version of the reference
        journal - The name of the journal in which the reference has been published
        title - The title of the reference
        repository - The URL of the repository for the reference
        isbn - The ISBN of the reference
        license - The SPDX license short identifier for the license under which the reference has been published
        end - The page number where the reference ends
        institution - The institution where the reference has been produced or published
        repositoryArtifact - The URL of the artifact repository for the reference
        dateReleased - The date on which the reference has been released
        recipients - The recipients of the reference (e.g., for personal communications)
        numberVolumes - The number of volumes making up the collection in which the reference has been published
        pages - The total number of pages of the reference
        issueDate - The publication date of the issue of a periodical in which the reference has been published
        editorsSeries - The editors of the series in which the reference has been published
        abbreviation - The abbreviation for the reference
        abstractString - An abstract or description for the reference
        database - The database which provides the reference
        medium - The medium of the reference
        section - The section of a work which is the reference (e.g., for book sections)
        issueTitle - The title of the issue of a periodical in which the reference has been published
        pmcid - The PMCID of the reference
        dataType - The data type of the reference (e.g., for data sets)
        yearOriginal - The year in which the reference has originally been published
        entry - An entry in a collection which constitutes the reference
        volume - The volume of a periodical in which the reference has been published
        filename - The filename of the reference
        notes - Notes pertaining to the reference
        doi - The DOI of the reference
        Throws:
        InvalidDataException - on invalid data and resulting parse errors, e.g., for date/time parses or malformed URLs
